    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[4th June 2021, Nigeria]In comparison, Global Rights recorded at least 4 556 fatalities in 2020 (compared to 3 188 in 2018), of which 3 858 (compared to 2 707 in 2018) were civilians, as a result of ‘mass atrocities’ defined as violent attacks, clashes, terrorism, kidnappings, and extrajudicial killings, with Borno state continuing to record the highest number of fatalities (1 176), followed by Kaduna state (628). Nigeria Watch recorded 2 677 ‘lethal incidents’ in 2020 during which 12 318 people were killed (compared to 11 277 recorded ‘violent deaths’ in 2019)539, with Borno state recording the highest number of fatalities (3 069 deaths), followed by Kaduna (1 346), Katsina (1 099), Zamfara (831) and Niger (547)."/>
